<subSubSection id="5F06BC3B72143E7881283F31D0E14217" pageId="0" pageNumber="133" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E496B0FB7A1524828FDDDD45BDA3C74E" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7C2C711A9BA24031D7BE9659D205C97" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">
This species is currently known only from the type locality, i.e. Huanglian Shan National Nature Reserve, Yunnan, China. Since this locality is very close to the border of China and Vietnam and the habitat is similar and continuous, this species is probably also distributed in Vietnam. It grows on the trunks of trees like 
<taxonomicName id="C659D71E629E7CB134E04A9CA4F217DD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Schima" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schima wallichii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wallichii">
<emphasis id="2F81EF3FC2B26611710EC5A1D910372B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">Schima wallichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Korth. or 
<taxonomicName id="ADB4935765797A8F56192C628F6E468C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Lithocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lithocarpus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A475D9DE09E3ED3C8A557C07E53EF634" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">Lithocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. under broadleaved forests at an elevation of ca. 1800 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
